When a TestNG class extends another test class,
TestNG inherits all @Test methods from the parent class automatically.

So:

BaseClass defines @Test placeOrder() and @Test ordersHistory()

ErrorsValidation extends BaseClass

TestNG now treats both methods as part of ErrorsValidation too

That’s why you see:

placeOrder() (BaseClass)

placeOrder() (ErrorsValidation)

ordersHistory() (BaseClass)

ordersHistory() (ErrorsValidation)

Total = duplicates = 8 total test executions.

Solution 1 — Make BaseClass a Pure Base (No @Test methods)
Solution 2 — Keep BaseClass Tests, but Prevent Inheritance
Solution 3 — Keep BaseClass abstract

